reviews.text: Their new location allows for a family-friendly dine-in spot. It is exceptionally beautiful. They have board games for families to play and have multiple TVs with something on for everyone. The staff is always pleasant and welcoming. The food is always phenomenal. I absolutely reccomend this pizza to anyone looking to have a pizza night.

I got the Big Juan!
This location is pickup and delivery only but it has the same signature delicious pizzas as the other locations!
I got mine during one of the busiest times of the season and got great service and my pizza in less than 30 minutes! All things said, an awesome experience!

My husband bought pizza tonight and he‚Äôs a big foodie, loves to eat‚Ä¶. We paid $60 for a large pizza, salad, and wings. Salad was very small, pizza was not good at all. The big guy likes to eat and only ate two pieces.

I recently learned of the personal size pizza offering during lunch, game changer for me as I didn't come here often before due to even a small being a bit much. But this is *perfect* and now I have an excuse to visit frequently.

Clean spot, nice natural light, some tasty sauces to add to pizzas, big salads.
We are here on Sunday night light. The staff was sweet and accommodating. Reasonable price. Love the cheesy bread. Enjoyed the games you can bring to your table! Not a crumb was left!

detailedReviews.author: Doc E
detailedReviews.text: Great wings and a extremely friendly staff but I did not care much for the pizza. The pizza crust is a little bland and doughy the sauce is not great and the toppings just kind of sit on top instead of working well with the pizza. 4 years later and the pizza is much improved the staff is very friendly and the star of the show is the meatballs they are amazing. Next time I cook spaghetti for my family I am 100% ordering meatballs my wife and I are not sharing with the kids either they are too good the share.

detailedReviews.author: Rosalie Stone
detailedReviews.text: I always order from Odd Moe each time I crave Pizza. They've been the most consistent of all the Pizzeria's around.

detailedReviews.author: Diana B
detailedReviews.text: Thought I would try them 1 more time because they were a good pizza 2 or 3 years ago. Got the confirmation at 1:46 pm with a 3:20 pm delivery. Silly me I thought that they would make it on a time schedule that did not allow it to sit for maybe an hour and 20 minutes. But I was wrong. So for $58.00 I got a large, slightly warm Borg pizza. Some Luke warm meatballs and a fairly cold garden salad. Sadly, the Romain was pretty brown for about half of the salad. Is it because of the delivery option? Is it because our local restaurants just don't have the right tools any more? That's just too much money for poor product.

detailedReviews.text: Odd Moe's Pizza - Deliv...

detailedReviews.author: Sarah Dabney
detailedReviews.text: We just moved here. Been trying alllll the pizzas. Odd moes def delivers the best pizza. Best. And the delivery is as fast. We‚Äôve had it 3 times now and tonight was especially good so shout out to those working tonight. We‚Äôve found our pizza night craving place. Thank you!

detailedReviews.author: Goob M.
detailedReviews.text: I am very glad to say this place has made a return to its former good-ness. There for a while it was constantly pretty awful. Each time we ordered the pizza(s) was very dry, below minimal sauce amount, hardly any topping (seemingly even less if paid for additional toppings). During this time period it truly had no flavor giving Little Ceasars a run for its money. But now it's back, our favorite pizza location has made a comeback to the good 'ol days where there is actual flavor again and a set standard.

detailedReviews.author: jeaneen Houston
detailedReviews.text: So we ordered online for delivery about 7pm. And they put our estimated delivery time was 9pm. When I called in about 910 to see what was going on. They said that the online orders got pushed out on their time because of being so busy tonight. I was informed the food was on the way. When it got here part of our order had been left at odd Moe's. So the driver refunded that part. The quality of the food is good. But from now on our we will not be ordering from them online. Since it doesn't seem to matter. It will be a long while till we get their pizza ever again. There are other places close to us that are about the same price and better quality.

detailedReviews.author: Hot Rod
detailedReviews.text: I've ordered pizza from here for years.  Never thought it was the best, but I seem to be ok with it.  About a month ago I got a pizza that was really very very good, and the crust wasn't as tough as normal.  Since that time I've order that same pizza, and a different type. These last 2 were not very good at all. The sauce was nasty.  My wife would not eat it. To top it off, when you pay by debit they ask for a tip starting a 18% on up. Tips was all one of the employees could talk about.  I'm done here.  Won't be back again.

detailedReviews.author: tim clark

detailedReviews.author: Byron watson

Staff are nice and the pizza is ok. They are the only people in Oregon doing a Chicago style pizza.
If you call over tje phone and pick up your own pizza the staff will hook you up with the coupon deal. Just let them know your read on Google reviews and someone said I needed the coupon deal.
If you have never tried a Chicago style pizza please give it a try. Sausage, pepperoni, and sometype of veggie.
Good luck and I wish everyone well out there on the hunt for pizza.

detailedReviews.text: Great variety of pizza.  Love the home-made feel.  Huge chicken wings.  I must admit I also like Dominos,  but there is no beating these guys.  I attached photos of the chicken wings, poppers, large pepperoni/Canadian bacon pizza, and a two liter bottle of soda.  Everything was perfectly cooked and tasty.  I now have the thighs to prove it.

detailedReviews.author: Rick Cobb
detailedReviews.text: When I moved here they were very good, now they are cold and soggy every time. When I called to complain I heard them laughing and saying "no no no I don't want to talk to him" and " come on it's always funny" I used to love them but will never get another dollar from me.

detailedReviews.author: Jerry Miller

detailedReviews.author: Alisha Fitts
detailedReviews.text: Only went in for their cheesy garlic bread, but when I got there I wasn't too sure if I should go in or not because I was already late and they were SLAMMED (who am I kidding?! I wasn't gonna pass on garlic cheesy bread)! The employees seemed too work very well with one another and were nice and respectful when interacting with their customers, and although working under a good amount of orders, it took minimal time to fulfill and send out completed tickets for in house and delivery. I'm pleasantly surprised at how well the rush was handled!!! AND the food was incredible, as always!
